review_blob: Bottle and draft at SL... Poured into a snifter, monster rocky head that sticks around....strong lacing left on the glass. Bright orange in color, with a red hue. Nose of pine needles and fruit. Taste is classic big west coast double IPA. Tons of tropical fruits, grass, pine needles, dry and not sugary sweet...Oily hop presence. Body is light and easy to drink for a beer that is over 11%. Smooth and dry. Overall: I havent had a big DIPA like this in a while.. reminds me some classic and while I love this style. Great beer, go ahead a pick some up!

Bottle picked up at the brewery. Hazy orange/lemon, not much head. Nose of lemon, hay, grass and tartness. Taste is light tartness...lots of lemon, grass. Body is light.... reminds me of a berliner. Very drinkable, summer esque brew...Overall: Good stuff

Bottle picked up at SL... Hazy orange color, small head that faded fast. Great nose of coffee beans and chocolate! Taste is initially chocolate followed by a sweet coffee taste. Slight malt, flowers bready notes. Body is light and easy to drink. I didnt think I would like this but its a solid brew. Odd combination of coffee and chocolate in a blonde beer? Brewers pulled it off well.

Bottle picked up at SL.... clear-ish orange color, small head. Nose of funk, slight cheese. Never heard of lingonberries..... taste is funky sour. Fruit notes. Light body, easy drinker... Overall unique/odd but enjoyable. Thanks to Matt for the rec

Bottle from SL... Light orange in color, small head. Nose of light grass, hay, pine.... Taste is average for a session IPA... on the malty, bready side, light grass hay. Meh... Medium to light body. Overall nothing wrong with it.... but very forgettable. Cheers to Matt for the rec.

Draft at F&M; 4th Anv party... Had about three 8oz Hapis. Bright orange in color, decent head. Nose of citrus, fresh hay, grass, lemon, tartness... Taste is lovely. Light refreshing tartness, lemon, hay, earthy, spices, and oak notes.. Body is light and bubbly, perfect carbonation. Overall: Good shit, wish I had a bottle

Bottle at Forest and Main... Big old bubbly beer, light straw color... Nose of light grass, tart, hay, earth notes... Taste is classic saison with a slight tartness. Lots of earth notes, tartness upfront, hay, and citrus/grass. Bottle says barrel aged but not sure what type and its not traceable.... Body is light and refreshing, lots of carbonation. Overall easy drinker, good stuff!

Draft at StateLine.... Pours a reddish hue... Small head. Nose of sour cherries. Taste is a big sour punch in the face... makes you go "whooooo"... Cherries are noticeable but take a back seat to the big sourness on this beer. Body is really light and refreshing, easy to drink. Overall good stuff..

Draft/growler at StateLine... Poured in to a snifter. Nose of juicy blood oranges! Average looking brewski... Light orange in color, small head. Taste is nice IPA... Blood oranges stands out initially, followed by a hop burst, light crystal malts... easy drinker. This beer is juicy....Medium body, clean and crisp, alcohol well hidden. Overall: I can dig it

Oh yeah i can dig it! Bottle from SL.. Poured in to a snifter, big head old rocky head tan colored head. Black in color.... Good nose of hops and coffee. Taste follows the nose... Big coffee notes with a strong bitterness.. Medium smooth body. Overall, good chite.

Bottle from SL... Nose of fruity characters, pineapples, mangos and hops. Pours a light orange in color, decent head. Taste is fruity, slight pineapple, lots of tropical notes. The hops take a back seat in this beer, it does not have the hop punch sculpin has. Nice easy drinking beer. Overall not a good as the regular version or habanero

Draft at Teresas in Wayne PA. Nice pour, light black in color, small mocha colored head. Nose is light hop presence, heavy roasted malts. Taste reminds me of a porter. Lots of roasted malts, light hop bitterness. Light coffee and chocolate notes. Smooth silky body, easy to drink. Overall, great beer for its style/category.

Bottle from SL, draft at McGlynns. Nice pour into a snifter! Big rocky head and strong lacing on the glass. Light orange in color. Good nose as well... lots of juicy fruits... Tangerine, pineapple, grapefruit... Taste follows the nose.. lots of juicy fruit notes...grapefruit, pineapple, oranges, tangerines, light hop presence with a slight malty bread notes. Body is light... summer brew? Overall very enjoyable!

Bottle picked up at StateLine. Poured in to a snifter, big old rocky head, strong lacing left on the glass. Big nose of spruce needles. Smells like douglas fir. Taste is spruce and douglas fir...taste like bathroom cleaner? Not sure if like it.... medium body... easy drinker... but just not my cup of tea. unique but not me. Love the name.

Bottle via StateLine. Smells just like a Peanut butter and jelly sandwich! Taste is sweet raspberry, followed by a peanut butter jelly taste. Very unique but too sweet. 4 oz was enough for me. Glad I shared with a friend.

Can from StateLine.. Poured in to a snifter, small thin brown head that faded fast. Strong lacing left on the glass, black in color. Good nose of fresh coconut! Taste is a dry, ashy, chalky, roasted malts, chocolate and strong presence of coconut. Body is on the light side, easy drinker. Overall, unique brew.... good stuff!
beer_name: Oskar Blues / Shamrock Death By Coconut

review_blob: Bottle via StateLine. Poured in to a snifter, bright orange in color, decent head. Nose is light floral, tropical fruits, pineapple, mango, spices, earthy finish. Body is clean and light, easy drinker. Solid beer.

Bottle via SL. Poured in to a snifter, black in color almost no head. Smells solid, cold coffee, coffee beans. Taste is some slight spices, coffee and more coffee. Wish the body was a little more chewy or viscous but overall a solid beer.

Bottle from StateLine. Great nose, cocoa, coffee beans, chocolate, creamy milk, spices...etc. Pours a dark black color, small head. Taste is coffee beans, chocolate, cinnamon, spices, milk and peppers. All blended together very well. Body is creamy and smooth, enjoyable brew. I could put a couple of these down.. Overall good chite!
beer_name: Chris Banker / Insurgente / Stone Xocoveza Mocha Stout

review_blob: Bottle from Stateline.... ~ 1 year old.. Lots of rum/barrel notes on the nose. Looks solid..... Bright orange, decent head. Taste light spices, pumpkin note with a nice touch of rum but not over whelming. Body is average, smooth and easy to drink a for a beer that is over ten percent. Glad I tried it but prefer the regular version of pumking!
beer_name: Southern Tier Rum Barrel Aged Pumking

review_blob: Can from Berttttt! Poured into a snifter, bright orange in color with a good head. Smells nice, pineapple, mango, tropical fruits. Taste follows the nose... Lots of tropical fruits, mango, light peach, pineapple with a nice bitter after taste. Nice west coast style. Body is medium, smooth, easy drinker. Overall... very enjoyable ... highly recommend it! Thanks Bert!

Can from Bert! Dark orange in color, small head. Poured into snifter. Decent nose of musty hops..... citrus, piney. Taste is a solid IPA. Good amount of citrus, grapefruit, grass followed by a big malt backbone. On the sweeter side. Body is kind of chewy, rye notes? Overall solid brewski. thanks Bertttttttttt!

Bottle from StateLine. Solid nose of pumpkin, spices with a light floral note. Dark orange in color, small head but this was drank on the warmer side ~50 degrees. Taste is more on the pumpkin side than an IPA. Good amount of pumpkin, spices, cinnamon, nutmeg... followed by a floral bitterness. Slight burn from the alcohol. Overall: Arguably my two favorite styles... Pumpkin vs IPA.... not a bad one-two combo.

Bottle from SL... Poured in to a snifter, small head. Smells fruity.... nose of straw, light grass but tropical fruits dominate the nose. Taste is dry, tropical fruits. Body is lighter, smooth and easy to drink for a DIPA. West coast like? Tasty little brewski. " I approve this beer"

Can... took a case of this on a trip to the North Maine Woods, my favorite by a good margin. Nice bright orange color, decent little head. Solid nose of fresh hops/resin slight dankness. Taste is bright citrus notes, light pine, light dank presence. Tons of flavor for such an easy "quaffable" brew. Great beer at a perfect moment in time. Oh yeah.... and I was digging the label.

Can.... Took a case of this to the North Maine Woods for a ten day excursion. Looks like a Pilsner, taste like a Pilsner. Palate is wet. Hard to find a bad Sierra Nevada beer. Not my favorite beer by all means but pretty solid example of what a lager should taste like.

On draft at Lansdale beer fest 6-27-2015. Light brown in color, not much head. Smelled good, dark fruits, malty. Taste is classic Belgian ale. Smooth, dark fruits, light banana, flowers, spices, yeast notes, malt. Body is on the lighter side but very enjoyable. Enjoyed a 3-4 oz sample 3x.*********   I have been looking for this beer for a while now...surprised it was at a beer fest in PA..... 1st reason..the only trappist brewery in the states and the second reason is the name. It was not a let down and would like to get my hands on a bottle. Miss you Spencer!

Draft/growler at StateLine... Light yellow color, small head but the growler was a couple days old. Nice nose... Tons of hops presence. Taste is light and grassy. Lots of flavor for a beer that is only 4 percent. Surprised that is so well balanced. Nice bready crystal malt presence..Body is light but drinkable... quench your thirst. Good chite

Bottle. Poured in to a snifter, monster rocky head that sticks around. Nose of bright fresh hops. Light lemony zest with in the nose. Taste is nice dry saison, earthy, grassy, spices, nice hop character, light lemon peel, some tropical fruits and some black pepper. Tons of flavor going on. Light body easy to drink. Soft carbonation. Overall: Great beer all around. Very drinkable

Bottle picked up at SL. Big ole" head, strong lacing left on the snifter. Copper orange in color. Sweet hop notes on the nose. Taste is classic Stone... sweet hoppy presence. Pine, grass, light tropical fruits but definitely hop forward, but not a harsh bitterness. Surprisingly easy to drink for a beer close to nine percent. Overall I give it two thumbs up!

Draft and growler at stateline. Bright orange in color, small head and strong lacing left on the glass/snifter. Nose of lemon, wet hops, tropical fruits...Taste is lots of lemon, tropical fruits, very juicy with out being bitter. Body is medium, surprisingly easy to drink for a beer close to 8 percent. Overall: Stone doesnt make a bad IPA.

Bottle via StateLine. Poured aggressively into a stem glass. Big ole head, that faded fast. Clear-ish yellow color. Good lacing left on the glass. Nose of flowers, fruits, bread or biscuits. Taste is flower hops, light fruits, clean malt presence to balance it out. Light body but not watery. Goes down easy. Overall; nice session brew

Draft at the Victory in Kennett Square. Light yellow, slightly hazy. Served too cold and a little too much Co2. Smells decent. Light fruits, light hop presence on the nose. Taste was a little on the watery side. Not really hop forward. Tropical fruits...little grassy. Body on the light side..... Mehhhh...
beer_name: Victory Dtown Draft Moxee Session IPA

review_blob: Bottle via SL.. poured in to a snifter. Decent lacing left on the glass. Light golden orange color, small head. Nose of some fruity hops. Bready crystal malty nose. Taste is light tropical fruits, nice hop presence/bitterness. Alcohol well hidden, easy drinker. Overall good brewski. * rest in peace big Spencer! Miss you!
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - The Calling IPA

review_blob: Bottle from SL. Light orange in color... decent head. Nose of hop resin. Taste is not bitter but tons of hop flavor. Crystal malt presence. Well balanced easy to drink. Another good beer from SN.

Can from sloth. Pours a decent orange color with a frothy head. Nose of hops, slight fruity notes. Taste is a classic east coast IPA... Hoppy but the malt presence takes away from taste and over all experience of a DIPA. Taste is average. Medium body. Overall nothing to write home about. Thanks to bert for the can!

Can from sloth! Light yellow in color. Nice head. Nose of some salty ocean water and soured milk. Taste is a very light hay/straw, slightly salty taste. Light spices. Little spoiled milk and acidity. Tons of flavor for a 4 percenter!  Body is light and easy to drink while refreshing! Great summer beer. Could drink it all day. Thanks Berttttt!
Draft at two stones in Kennett. Funky red color which I wasnt expecting. Nose of slight tart blueberries. Taste is fruity... Not farmhouse at all. Meh.... not much to write about. Not a fan

Bottle (12oz) from stateline. Poured into a snifter big ole rocky head that sticks around, black in color. Lacing left all over the glass. Nose of roasted malts and fresh hops. Reminds me of a porter... nose is chalky/ashy. Taste is initially lots of roasted malts, followed by a nice hop presence but not over whelming or IPA like. Dry and easy drink. Overall nice black IPA even though I wish they didnt call it that. Pairs well with Bob Seger night moves or Jimis night bird flying!

Bottle picked up at StateLine.. Poured in to a snifter... big ole rocky head, that sticks around. Light orange color which is slightly murky. Nose of tropical fruits...pineapple, banana. Taste is tropical fruits... light pineapple, pear, banana, light bitterness/hop presence in the aftertaste. Nice malty body. Reminds me Sam Adams Noble pils. Easy to drink. Cant say enough good things about this beer... definitely exceeded expectations!

Bottle shared by Matt at StateLine... Murky/cloudy orange color... with a small head. Nose of orange peel, earthy/dirt notes, black pepper, saison spices... Taste of light wheat/hay, earthy saison spices, black pepper, lemon, slight hop presence with a nice tartness to it. Body is medium but really easy to drink. Overall great beer as most of Hill farmstead beers are. Thanks to matt for being so generous and sharing! PEPPER!

Bottle via SL... Looks like a barleywine.. Dark orange in color... meduim head...Great nose of green apples and tropical fruits. I was expecting an abundant amount of hops in the taste but not the case.. not that bitter. Lots of fruity notes. Extra smooth... more of an DIPA... best of both worlds... smoothness of a barleywine with out the harshness of the high alcohol content brews. Huge malt character with out being sweet. Really well balanced. Maybe I should age a bottle or two. Overall good stuff

Growler from stateline.. Pours a golden orange in color, decent head. Great nose of seeping juicy wet fresh grapefruit. Lots of lemon, orange and tropical fruit notes as well. Grapefruit grinds just punch you in the nose. Taste is tons of grapefruit, tropical fruit notes but lacking the classic sculpin hop presence. Noticeable bitterness, slight grass notes. Body is smooth and easy to drink. Overall... very enjoyable but I like the habanero and regular version better!

Draft at F&M.; Pours a light black color. Nose of sour cherries. Taste is unique for a saison. Lots of dark fruits, cherries, chocolate, roasted malts, coffee grinds. Followed by a slightly sour/tart after taste with just the right amount of sour green apple puckering taste. As it warmed up I though it lost some of the sourness. Body is light and refreshing, perfect amount of carbonation. I like the low alcohol content. Overall unique twist on a saison. Very enjoyable!

Draft at F&M..; nose has light hop presence bready malt notes. Taste is classic English pale ale. Boring....which is why I dont enjoy them that much. Light hops, bready malt notes. Nothing really stands out. Light body easy drinker. Overall this is a good example of what an EPA should taste like but I just think they are plain jane.

Draft at F&M.; Pours a hazy orange, decent head. Nose of lemon/mellon hay and grass. Taste is a well balanced saison. Good amount of grass/hay hops...light mellon/lemon. Slight tart notes. Light body and really easy to drink. Overall decent brewski

Bottle picked up at SL. Bright orange in color decent head. Love the nose... Pineapples and fruit followed by a slight hint of green leaves. Taste is very unique for an IPA... Lots of pineapple, tropical fruits... followed by a perfect amount of green leaves/tea. The green tea leaves take a back seat to the tropical fruits and really balance it out. Super easy to drink, I had to double check the bottle when I saw it was listed on RB at over 10%. Mellow, more of an IPA. Overall cant say enough good things about this beer.
beer_name: Baird / Ishii / Stone Japanese Green Tea IPA 10.1% (2015)

review_blob: Bottle (2013) shared by wolf. Nose of slight smoke/peat/moss.... Pours a muddy red color. Nose of bourbon/vanilla. Taste reminds me of a barley wine... to be more exact north coast old stock barrel aged barley wine. I love the strong malt presence...light smoke/moss. Tons of dark fruits with a slight burn from the high alcohol content. Body is super smooth and will probably get even better with age. Wish I had a bottle to age but oh well. ****good night to a classy lady known as Annie. Rest in peace.

Bottle (2013) shared by wolf! Nose of spice and peppers! Pours a murky red color. Taste like hot wings! Burns like the dickens! This one burns with an intense burning on the back of the throat. I will probably pay for this tomorrow! This is not for the faint hearted or even some one who wants to experiment. Medium sticky body, enjoyable... smooth but the heat from the peppers is the only thing you can focus on. Love or hate it.... I loved it!

Bottle (2013) shared by wolf. Pours a murky red color almost no head. Nose is off the charts! Tons of vanilla/bourbon and spicy peppers. Taste is not for freshman...strictly lineman... Tons of heat on this big boy. Spicy notes on the front of your palate... burning on the back of your throat. INTENSE... Sipper... Medium slightly sticky body but it is hard to focus on anything but the heat from the beer. This is a love or hate beer. I loved it, but share the heat with a friend!
